-- BYD shares down more than 7 percent on reports of weak March earnings
-- By Natalie Thomas
-- Tue Apr 15, 2014 03:25AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, April 15 (Reuters) - Hong Kong listed shares in BYD Co Ltd <1211.HK> <002594.SZ>  fell more than 7 percent on Tuesday after media reports that March sales figures for the Warren Buffett-backed Chinese carmaker were down 24 percent on the same period last year.

Chinese media and the Wall Street Journal reported that the company sold 39,300 vehicles globally in March, citing an emailed statement from the company.  BYD did not immediately respond to requests for comment.  Shares listed on the mainland fell 3 percent.